# Changelog

## 0.2.0 (2026-01-04)

GPU acceleration release.

### Added
- WGPU GPU backend for cross-platform GPU support (Metal, Vulkan, DirectX)
- Hybrid GPU approach: EC scalar multiplication on GPU, hashing/encoding on CPU
- WGSL compute shader for secp256k1 EC operations (`shaders/ecmult_hybrid.wgsl`)
- C FFI bindings for wgpu-native (`cbits/wgpu_vanity.c`)
- Haskell FFI bindings (`lib/Crypto/Bitcoin/Vanity/FFI/WGPU.hsc`)

### Performance
- GPU throughput: ~88,000 keys/sec on Apple M4 Max (Metal backend)
- CPU throughput: ~560 keys/sec per thread
- GPU speedup: ~157x over single CPU thread, ~10x over 16-core CPU

### Build Flags
- `wgpu`: Enable WGPU backend (requires wgpu-native library)

### Usage
```bash
# Build with WGPU support
cabal build -f wgpu

# Run with GPU backend (P2WPKH or P2TR only)
vanity -b wgpu "^bc1q" -t p2wpkh
vanity -b wgpu "^bc1p" -t p2tr
```

### Limitations
- P2PKH (Base58) addresses only supported on CPU backend
- Requires wgpu-native library installed on system

## 0.1.0 (2026-01-04)

Initial release.

- Support for P2PKH (Base58), P2WPKH (Bech32), P2TR (Bech32m) address types
- Mainnet and testnet support
- POSIX regex pattern matching with case-insensitive option
- Multi-threaded CPU backend
- CLI with progress reporting
- WIF and hex private key output
